args: It's been a long time, Cassandra.
Heavens, this can't be! How did you...?
Or perhaps it would be better to treat\nthis as an introduction... You may\ncall me Audric. It is an honor to meet you.

I am aware of the imposition I am causing,
but I must ask your assistance regardless.
Indeed, the salvation of both this kingdom
and this entire world relies on it.
You're the same as ever, aren't you?\nAll these years later, and it's straight to\nbusiness without a hint of romance.
I am truly gladdened to see you again,\nbut I fear these other pressing issues\nmust take precedence over my feelings.
And you're still stubborn as an old mule!\n*sigh* Fine, then. Flap your gums a spell\nand tell me what you need.
...A way to sever the chain of causality?\nIs that all? Mayhap you'd like me to\nmove the stars around while I'm at it!
If I am not mistaken, you have studied\nmagic relating to time for quite a while.
Even the smallest of clues could be of use.\nIf you know anything—anything at all—\nI beg of you to tell me now.
Oh, I reckon I might know something.
A way to sever the chain of causality.
I said I KNOW a way to do it—I didn't say\nI was going to TELL it to you.
Don't get your smallclothes in a bunch!\nI'm getting to the point.
Now then! To sever one's chain of causality\nis to sever one's link to their world.
If you were to pass through time after that,\nyou'd be lost to this world forever.
This matter involves the very existence\nof this world itself. My eventual fate is\nnothing when compared to that.
Tsk! You haven't learned a thing.
You talk about ＂the kingdom＂ and ＂the\nworld＂ as if they exist independently\nof these actions you're planning.
But what happens to this here world if\nyou're no longer in it? What happens to\nall of the PEOPLE here? Mmm?
But this is the only path left to me.
Why did you bother to save these people?\nWhy did you bring them all this way?
And how do you think they'll feel if you\ncarry out this plan and abandon them?
I KNOW you hadn't—which is why we'll\ntalk about this after you cool your heels\nand give it a good long think.
Hey, did you hear about Audric?
It sounds like we've come all this way\njust so he can find a way to run off to\nsome ＂other world.＂
You got me. All I know is that once he\nleaves, he can't ever come back.
We go back to living in terror under the\nEmpire...
Maybe there's some way we can convince\nhim to give up on this fool notion.
Yes! You said he's just LOOKING for a way\nto visit this new world, right? If so,\nthat means there's still time.
Maybe the person he's talking to right now\nknows how to visit the other world.
You mean the sorceress? I heard she's\nabout the smartest person anywhere.
But what on earth would such a powerful\nsorceress be doing all the way out here?
She's right. It must be a trick.
Audric would never leave us behind!
So if we get rid of that sorceress—
We have to kill the witch...
It is unusual to see you in\nsuch a state of worry.
And I'm simply worrying as I always do.\n...Worrying and then making mistakes\nregardless.
Tell me your mind, Zodiark.\nIs what I am doing truly right?
Or, even if it isn't, am I at least going\nto save people by continuing on my\ncurrent course?
Will it only create more suffering?
Even if you cross through the veil and\naccomplish your mission, it might not\nchange the fate of the people here.

However, such things are unknown until
the moment they happen. That is why the
Auspex herself passed through time,
and why the Emperor gave chase.

In other words, there is no way to know
for certain if I will succeed or not.
Is that really worth the effect it will have
on the people here?
You carry too many burdens. By rights,\nthere is no need for you to take on\nso many that are not your own.
Perhaps I need to rethink things after all.\nOr at least forestall my plan until I've\nfound a safe refuge for these people.
By the goddess, Notte! You're bleeding!
＂Kill the witch,＂ they said...\n＂Kill the w-witch...＂
I tried to stop 'em, but...it was like\nthey were all... Nnnngh...
Fie, but these wounds are deep...\nHold on, Notte! Just hold on!
Don't worry, Notte. I'll heal you.
It's alright... You can stop, Audric...\nI'm...so tired...
